    "body": "I was working on adding `--annotate` to IPython's `%%cython` magic (which is clearly based off of `Cython.Build.Inline.cython_inline`), and figured that it would be a simple change... just set `ctx.options.annotate = True`.  But this did not work....\n\nAfter a bit of poking around, I discovered that the `cythonize` does not actually use the `ctx` parameter that it was passed.  Instead, it expects something more akin to `**ctx.options.__dict__`.\n\nSome reworking here is required.  I think the easiest option would be to not even create the `ctx` in `cython_inline` and just pass the options upon which it is based.\n\nMigrated from http://trac.cython.org/ticket/781",
